Vice President M. Hamid Ansari will dedicate the K.R. Narayanan National Institute of Visual Science and Arts at Thekkumthala near here on Monday. The Vice-President will arrive at the temporary helipad at the St. Thomas College grounds at Pala by 2.45 p.m. and the campus by 3.15 p.m. taking the Mutholi- Kozhuvanal-Pallickathode route. After the inaugural ceremony, he will move to Pala and from there to Kochi by helicopter.The police have strengthened security. According to a press note here on Sunday, the traffic on the route will be regulated during the period.Governor P. Sathasivam, Chief Minister Oommen Chandy, Education Minister P.K. Abu Rabb, Transport Minister Thiruvanchoor Radhakrishnan, Jose K. Mani, MP, K. Suresh Kurup, MLA, and others will speak on the occasion of the dedication ceremony. The foundation stone for the institute was laid by the then Union Minister for Information and Broadcasting Priya Ranjan Dasmunsi in 2005.